  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Federal contracting in Arizona through FY2026 to date shows $20.9B in contract obligations across 13,523 awards, with an average award size of $1.5M and obligations down 10.2% year over year. The Department of Defense dominates buying with $13.8B in obligations, followed by the Department of Homeland Security at $6B; other agencies contribute smaller but material amounts such as the Department of Veterans Affairs at $346M and the General Services Administration at $184M. Top vendors include RAYTHEON COMPANY at $4.7B, TRIWEST HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE CORP at $4.6B, and FISHER SAND & GRAVEL CO at $4.5B. Industry concentrations highlight Commercial and Institutional Building Construction at $6B, Direct Health and Medical Insurance Carriers at $4.6B, and Guided Missile and Space Vehicle Manufacturing at $3.6B. Historical obligations by fiscal year show variability, including $23.3B in FY25 and $20.9B in FY26. This profile captures current-year totals that are partial (fiscal year to date) and reports contract obligations only.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "Which agencies drive federal contracting activity in Arizona?",
        "body": "The Department of Defense leads with $13.8B in obligations, and the Department of Homeland Security follows with $6B. Other agencies with notable obligations include the Department of Veterans Affairs at $346M, the General Services Administration at $184M, and the Department of Health and Human Services at $160M."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Who and what industries receive the largest contracting dollars in Arizona?",
        "body": "Top vendors by obligations are RAYTHEON COMPANY at $4.7B, TRIWEST HEALTHCARE ALLIANCE CORP at $4.6B, and FISHER SAND & GRAVEL CO at $4.5B. Leading industries by obligations are Commercial and Institutional Building Construction at $6B, Direct Health and Medical Insurance Carriers at $4.6B, and Guided Missile and Space Vehicle Manufacturing at $3.6B."
      }
    ]
  },
